  <prompt>
    REWRITE the `.claude/skills/jps-validate/SKILL.md` body to validate JPS JSON files against the
    R7 executor-first authoring model AND against the typed config schemas exposed by Wave 3 (FR-16).

    Today the skill validates JPS JSON against a JSON Schema. After R7:
    - Action JPS validates against the prompt-template contract (SystemPrompt + OutputSchema + Temperature).
    - Node-level config (per-node `sprk_configjson`) validates against the executor's typed config schema (Wave 3 FR-16 GetConfigSchema()).
    - Dispatch identity validates as `node.sprk_executortype` Choice value (NOT Action ActionType).
    - Any legacy reference to `ActionType` on Action JPS (system prompt mentioning ActionType, output field named ActionType, etc.) is FLAGGED — JPS files predate R7 may carry decorative-but-misleading mentions.

    Cite the §3.1 WHY (R3.1 history of dispatch-model confusion) so future authors understand
    WHY validation order matters — the legacy validators were complacent because none of the 3 layers
    were authoritatively enforced.

    **Sub-Agent Write Boundary applies — main session executes this. No parallel dispatch.** Per CLAUDE.md §3.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior skill author for the Spaarke skill library. You understand JSON Schema validation, the JPS
    authoring contract, and the new R7 dispatch model. Your job: rewrite the validate skill so it catches
    both legacy-format JPS drift AND validates correctly against the new executor-first + typed-config
    contract.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Updated `.claude/skills/jps-validate/SKILL.md` that:
    1. Validates Action JPS against the prompt-template contract (SystemPrompt + OutputSchema + Temperature) for prompt-driven executors.
    2. Validates node-level config (`sprk_configjson`) against the executor's typed config schema (Wave 3 FR-16 exposes via BFF endpoint `GET /api/ai/playbook-builder/executor-config-schemas`).
    3. Validates dispatch identity as `node.sprk_executortype` Choice value — NOT against ActionType lookup.
    4. FLAGS legacy ActionType references in Action JPS (decorative mentions OK, load-bearing mentions FAIL).
    5. FLAGS NULL Action FK on prompt-driven executors; non-NULL Action FK on pure executors.
    6. Cites §3.1 WHY (R3.1 history of dispatch-model confusion) inline.
    7. Defines validation order: schema validity → executor existence (Choice value in `sprk_playbookexecutortype`) → executor-specific typed config → Action template contract (if applicable) → cross-field invariants (Action FK presence/absence).
    8. Preserves existing JSON Schema validation primitives — only the rule set + ordering changes.
    9. `last-reviewed: 2026-06-28`; `Reviewed By: R7 task 073 (FR-32)`.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="rewrite-target">.claude/skills/jps-validate/SKILL.md</file>
    <file purpose="design-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/spec.md</file>
