  <context>
    <background>
      jps-validate runs JSON Schema + semantic validation on JPS files. R7 brings two reform pressures:
      1. Validation must check executor-first dispatch (`sprk_executortype` Choice on node), not Action lookup.
      2. Per-executor typed config schemas (Wave 3 FR-16) become validation targets.

      The validate skill is the gate that catches drift before deploy — task 075 (smoke test) runs this
      skill against representative playbooks to confirm Wave 7 rewrites are functional.

      Aligned with prior 3 rewrites (070, 071, 072) — same WHY citation, same terminology, same Action-template
      vs node-dispatch separation.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="072" status="prerequisite">jps-playbook-audit rewrite complete (aligned audit checklist).</dependency>
      <dependency task="024" status="prerequisite">Wave 2 single-hop dispatch refactor merged.</dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>Wave 3 (FR-16, tasks 030-036) ships the typed config schema endpoint — validate skill body should reference it as the validation target for node configs.</item>
      <item>Task 075 (smoke test) runs this skill on Daily Briefing DAILY-BRIEFING-NARRATE, Insights universal-ingest, chat-summarize.</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Rigor Declaration">
      Output: 🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: STANDARD · 📋 REASON: skill body rewrite (not ADR-bound code) · Proceeding with Step 0...
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Load context">
      Read project CLAUDE.md + spec.md FR-16, FR-32 + design.md §2 Invariants 1-5 + §3.1 WHY.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Read existing skill body">
      Read full current `.claude/skills/jps-validate/SKILL.md` (~12 KB). Note: validation steps, JSON Schema references, error reporting shape.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Read aligned prior rewrites">
      Read tasks 070, 071, 072 outputs for terminology + cross-reference alignment.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Inventory legacy validation references">
      Grep skill body for: "ActionType validation", "validate ActionType", "sprk_actiontypeid", "ActionType lookup row". List each; rewrite or delete.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Rewrite Purpose + Applies When">
      Reframe: "Validates JPS JSON files against the R7 executor-first authoring model + Wave 3 per-executor typed config schemas (FR-16). Catches drift before deploy."
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Define new validation order">
      The new validation pipeline (rewritten Workflow section):
      1. JSON Schema validity (existing — preserved).
      2. Executor existence: dispatch identity = `node.sprk_executortype` Choice; the value must be in the C# `ExecutorType` enum + the global `sprk_playbookexecutortype` Choice set.
      3. Executor-specific typed config: fetch schema from BFF `GET /api/ai/playbook-builder/executor-config-schemas`; validate node's `sprk_configjson` against the executor's schema.
      4. Action template contract (if applicable): if executor is prompt-driven (AiAnalysis, AiCompletion, AiEmbedding), the referenced Action's JPS validates SystemPrompt + OutputSchema + Temperature.
      5. Cross-field invariants: prompt-driven executors → Action FK non-NULL; pure executors → Action FK NULL.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Insert legacy-drift flag rules">
      Validation FAIL conditions for legacy drift:
      - Action JPS system prompt references "ActionType" or "sprk_actiontypeid" load-bearingly (decorative mention OK).
      - Action JPS output field named ActionType / ExecutorActionType / NodeType.
      - Node config carries `sprk_nodetype` (Dataverse column removed in Wave 4 schema cleanup).
      - Node config carries dispatch hints not driven by `sprk_executortype`.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Insert R7 dispatch-model section">
      Short subsection: "## The R7 dispatch model — what changed and why" citing design.md §3.1 + §2 Invariants 2-3 + 5. Explicit WHY: legacy validation was complacent because none of the 3 layers were authoritatively enforced; the new validation pipeline starts from the single-hop `sprk_executortype` and works outward.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Update error reporting shape">
      Errors carry: rule-id (e.g., `R7-V-04` for Action-FK mismatch), severity (FAIL / WARN), node path, recommended remediation. Add a deprecation legend: `LEGACY-` prefix for drift-pattern findings, `R7-` prefix for current-model validation.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Bump frontmatter">
      `last-reviewed: 2026-06-28`; `Reviewed By: spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7 task 073 (FR-32 — executor-first validation)`.
    </step>
    <step order="11" name="Verify acceptance">
      Re-read rewritten skill body. Confirm: (a) validation order has 5 stages with single-hop dispatch as the spine, (b) typed config schema endpoint (FR-16) referenced, (c) legacy-drift flags enumerated, (d) §3.1 WHY cited, (e) frontmatter bumped.
    </step>
    <step order="12" name="Update current-task.md + TASK-INDEX">
      Mark task 073 status complete; advance current-task.md to task 074.
    </step>
    <step order="13" name="Commit-deferred">
      DO NOT commit. Wave 7 commits at task 075.
    </step>
  </steps>

